cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE 

This paper discusses the use of algorithms to generate art and design, which falls under the category of computational creativity. The paper specifically focuses on incorporating characteristics of human creativity into the algorithm, which suggests a strong connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of fitness functions and evolutionary algorithms also suggests a connection to graphics (cs.GR) and computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of strategies characteristic of human artists, which could involve machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE).
